    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f9f70e49_863fb033",
        "filename": "src/gpu/ops/GrQuadPerEdgeAA.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-05T20:51:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Using the opposite edge, over the CW or CCW edge, is a key component to calculating the as-correct-as possible edges. If the degenerate edge should be AA\u0027ed, copying the opposite edge\u0027s direction lets us inset to match adjacent quads that must be AA\u0027ed on the same side.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 70,
        "startChar": 11,
        "endLine": 70,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "4551a9fe682011fd84bbab80f4a0aaadad3f8ce3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d4f2b013_f976099a",
        "filename": "src/gpu/ops/GrQuadPerEdgeAA.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 92,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-05T20:51:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I experimented with calculating dx and dy using a consistent left/right and top/bottom subtraction order (and then correcting signs to preserve CCW order), but it did not improve or hurt the seaming behavior in the compositor GMs.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 91,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 92,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "4551a9fe682011fd84bbab80f4a0aaadad3f8ce3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "400567b6_73eb46ff",
        "filename": "src/gpu/ops/GrQuadPerEdgeAA.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 154,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-05T20:51:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is likely that we could pick a conservative constant instead of calculating the actual edge lengths that would result. Would then trade off faster decision time for more quads going through the degenerate quad processing path.",
      "revId": "4551a9fe682011fd84bbab80f4a0aaadad3f8ce3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "12bce66e_acb7731d",
        "filename": "src/gpu/ops/GrQuadPerEdgeAA.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 217,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-05T20:51:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is one of the critical components of reducing the visible seaming between degenerate quads. Solving the system of equations for (a,b) can find a solution that uses two non-zero coefficients and then the final vertex corners for adjacent quads would have more substantial differences.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 217,
        "startChar": 11,
        "endLine": 217,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "4551a9fe682011fd84bbab80f4a0aaadad3f8ce3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
